text:
Consultancy for a group participating in a closed Kaggle competition. The main objective was to optimize out-of-sample prediction. At the end, the group gained confidence to employ their own strategies and further enhance the models, resulting in improved performance in the competition.








The solution involved three steps:
Careful exploratory data analysis (EDA) to gain a deep understanding of the data;
Training a set of models by running a notebook in the background utilizing Kaggle’s GPU, and;
Implementing a stacked models approach to combine the best-performing models.
